ELEGY II.

After the union of the crowns in 1603, Scotland could not now escape being drawn into the anti-French side of continental politics through its connection with her bigger sister, England. The war against France here deplored was that undertaken in July, 1626, when Buckingham was in the ascendant and made that hapless expedition to Rochelle and the Isle of Rhe. It lasted till May, 1629. In 1639, however, in the agony of the “Covenanff’ Rothes Loudoun and others appealed to Louis XIII. in virtue of the old alliance. See
